Tavatron tensed momentarily as he held her, this was something she hadn't 
quite expected. Dinobot had always stressed the fact that he despised 
emotions and closeness of any kind, especially when he was injured and 
feeling vulnerable, as did any warrior. However, she soon found herself 
relaxing in his strong grip, and hoping that this moment would never end. 
Her hands came to rest on his arms as she continued to gaze over at him, her 
eyes half-glazed in contentment. She had never felt like this before, so... 
so... peaceful.

Then the moment ended as quickly as it had begun, Dinobot once again 
retreating behind his barriers. With much reluctance Tavatron let her hands 
drop to her sides, a momentary look of dissapointment crossed her face but 
vanished a second later as she regained her composure.

Tavatron's ears swivled forward at the sound of an all to familiar voice. It 
was faint, but definitely there. The voice was quickly followed by the sound 
of gunfire as Tavatron rolled to the right, instinctively drawing her sword 
as she stood several feet from Dinobot, the shots barely passing overhead. 
She was all business now, the past moment lingering on the edges of her 
mind, as if it were a dream. She growled menecingly at Dark One, though her 
words were directed at Dinobot.

"You're in no condition to fight! I can handle myself! Take cover!"

Tavatron's scanners were still too weak to be of much use, but her eyesight 
and fighting abilities were capable of defending and holding her ground if 
necessary. Tavatron returned Dark One's fire, her optics glowing as she 
charged them, finally releasing two powerful blasts at Dark One, the first 
directed at his head, the second at his chest plate. Tavatron crouched 
beside a rather large bush, chancing a glance in Dinobot's direction.

"My scanners are down! How many are there besides this one?"
